<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 7: VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN
        BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND CRANKCASE - INSTALLATION - OIL PICKUP TUBE
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="install" graphiccount="3">
        <title>OIL PICKUP TUBE</title>
        <para>Perform the following steps:</para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install oil pick-up tube as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Install two (2) oil pick up tube mounting bolts and place new gasket into position (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600785">7.85</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Align holes of oil pick-up tube with two (2) holes in front cover. Secure oil pick-up
                    tube to front cover (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600786">7.86</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
                <figure id="ef1600784" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg6900" filename="../figeg6/EG6900.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.84 Checking Crankshaft End Play</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1600785" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5298" filename="../figeg5/EG5298.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.85 Installing Oil Pick-up Tube Gasket</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1600786" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5296" filename="../figeg5/EG5296.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.86 Securing Oil Pick-up Tube Mounting Bolts</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Align oil pick-up tube with support bracket and secure using one (1) bolt. Tighten to
                    special torque value. Refer to (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk document="e160_206.xml" xrefid="ef1600787">7.87</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Tighten two (2) front bolts to special torque value.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>IF STRESS OCCURS WHEN TIGHTENING THE MOUNTING BOLT OF THE OIL PICK-UP TUBE MOUNTING
                            BRACKET AFTER THE FRONT BOLTS ARE TIGHTENED, REPLACE TUBE. IF NO STRESS OCCURS, TORQUE THE
                            BRACKET BOLT TO THE SPECIAL TORQUE VALUE.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
            </step2>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
